President Biden has declared a major disaster in West Virginia due to severe storms, flooding, landslides, and mudslides that occurred in August 2022. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Jeffrey L. Jones has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.